text.tspan: Rate of acute flaccid paralysis from non-polio causes
This is an indicator of the level of screening for polio. It shows the number of cases of acute flaccid paralysis
(AFP) per 100,000 children, not attributed to polio, that were detected and reported to the WHO.
Note: The GPEI recommends that this rate should be at least 2 to indicate that AFP is being detected sufficiently.
